  "caption": "India or China for your next PCB order?\n\nWe put the real numbers side by side.\n\nLabor costs: India at ~$3/hr vs China at ~$5.80/hr. That's a 48% difference.\n\nBut cost per hour isn't the full picture.\n\nChina still leads on speed, volume scaling, and complex multilayer boards. Their supply chain ecosystem is decades ahead in integration.\n\nIndia's advantage? Lower tooling costs (great for startups and prototypes), zero or low import tariffs reducing your landed cost, and rapidly improving quality infrastructure backed by PLI incentives.\n\nThe smart move in 2026: use India for prototyping, low to mid volume, and cost sensitive production. Use China for high volume, tight deadlines, and advanced HDI boards.\n\nOr better yet, work with a partner like Cu Circuits who understands both ecosystems.\n\nWhat's your sourcing strategy? Drop it in the comments.\n\n#PCB #MakeInIndia #CuCircuits #PCBManufacturing #SupplyChain #HardwareStartup #IndiaManufacturing",
